261
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:55,933
<i>Don't you know Ruan Yu is my aim?</i>

262
00:20:59,760 --> 00:21:01,320
<i>I'm showing you mercy</i>

263
00:21:01,320 --> 00:21:03,120
<i>by not reporting you to Mr. Ruan.</i>

264
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:04,840
<i>If you keep pestering me</i>

265
00:21:04,840 --> 00:21:06,119
<i>and disturbing my studies,</i>

266
00:21:06,119 --> 00:21:08,760
<i>see you in the Dean's office.</i>

267
00:21:08,760 --> 00:21:10,240
<i>Ruan Yu! Ruan Yu!</i>

268
00:21:10,240 --> 00:21:12,040
<i>Ruan Yu!</i>

269
00:21:13,120 --> 00:21:14,500
<i>Also,</i>

270
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:16,360
<i>so what if you're like Dao Ming Si?</i>

271
00:21:16,360 --> 00:21:19,646
<i>I like Hua Ze Lei instead!</i>

272
00:21:27,600 --> 00:21:28,840
I'm sorry.

273
00:21:28,840 --> 00:21:30,866
What did you say?

274
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:34,039
I might be overcomplicating it.

275
00:21:34,039 --> 00:21:35,760
To put it simply,

276
00:21:35,760 --> 00:21:37,240
I think Poet's hero

277
00:21:37,240 --> 00:21:39,640
is too playful and childish.

278
00:21:39,640 --> 00:21:41,520
Aren't boys at that age

279
00:21:41,520 --> 00:21:43,600
all pretty much like that?

280
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:44,720
Not at all!

281
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:46,480
How could they be the same?

282
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:49,360
Poet's hero and mine are way too different!

283
00:21:49,360 --> 00:21:50,880
Look, he goes through so much trouble

284
00:21:50,880 --> 00:21:52,559
for fried chicken and coke.

285
00:21:52,559 --> 00:21:54,746
Isn't that playful?

286
00:21:55,759 --> 00:21:57,559
And to gain the heroine's favor,

287
00:21:57,559 --> 00:21:59,440
he puts on an act every day.

288
00:21:59,440 --> 00:22:00,800
Isn't that childish?

289
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:03,160
It's completely different from mine.

290
00:22:03,160 --> 00:22:05,000
Other plots can also prove this.

291
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:06,240
Wait, I'll show you.

292
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:07,847
No need.

293
00:22:07,847 --> 00:22:09,680
Let's call it a day.

294
00:22:09,680 --> 00:22:12,240
We'll continue some other day.

295
00:22:20,520 --> 00:22:23,253
He ended just like that?

296
00:22:25,480 --> 00:22:28,859
He seems a bit angry?

297
00:22:30,520 --> 00:22:33,300
I didn't mean him.

298
00:22:45,712 --> 00:22:49,966
[How to look nonchalant?]

299
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:52,477
<i>What are you dreaming about, buddy?</i>

300
00:22:52,477 --> 00:22:53,800
<i>If you ask such a question,</i>

301
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:57,073
<i>you're definitely not nonchalant this life.</i>

302
00:22:57,073 --> 00:23:00,386
<i>To look nonchalant,
you need grace and confidence.</i>

303
00:23:25,799 --> 00:23:28,220
How can I become nonchalant?

304
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:40,946
Something's wrong.

305
00:23:41,640 --> 00:23:44,226
Something's very wrong.

306
00:23:50,559 --> 00:23:53,906
<i>Lawyer Xu, are you asleep?</i>

307
00:24:11,040 --> 00:24:12,560
<i>It's nothing urgent.</i>

308
00:24:12,560 --> 00:24:14,480
<i>I just wonder</i>

309
00:24:14,480 --> 00:24:15,873
<i>if I said something wrong</i>

310
00:24:15,873 --> 00:24:18,160
<i>at today's meeting,</i>

311
00:24:18,160 --> 00:24:19,657
<i>and why you suddenly</i>

312
00:24:19,657 --> 00:24:21,899
<i>ended the video call.</i>

313
00:24:34,840 --> 00:24:36,000
<i>You didn't.</i>

314
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:38,960
<i>Other work came up at that time.</i>

315
00:24:40,720 --> 00:24:42,440
<i>But I do feel that,</i>

316
00:24:42,440 --> 00:24:44,766
<i>given your strong emotions</i>

317
00:24:44,766 --> 00:24:46,680
<i>to criticize that hero harshly,</i>

318
00:24:46,680 --> 00:24:49,120
<i>in a biased, irrational state,</i>

319
00:24:49,120 --> 00:24:52,000
<i>it's not a proper time to discuss.</i>

320
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:54,640
<i>So that was why.</i>

321
00:24:54,640 --> 00:24:57,220
He's way too strict.

322
00:25:02,160 --> 00:25:03,880
<i>Lawyer Xu, you misunderstood me!</i>

323
00:25:03,880 --> 00:25:05,200
<i>It was because</i>

324
00:25:05,200 --> 00:25:07,486
<i>I was eager to persuade you</i>

325
00:25:07,486 --> 00:25:09,740
<i>that they're different.</i>

326
00:25:23,920 --> 00:25:25,880
<i>I admit it.</i>

327
00:25:32,560 --> 00:25:35,680
She doesn't like me at all.

328
00:25:36,920 --> 00:25:39,253
How can I have a showdown now?

329
00:25:46,880 --> 00:25:48,560
Elite lawyers are really something.

330
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:51,313
They must remain objective
and rational at all times.

331
00:25:51,313 --> 00:25:54,439
Did he schedule another meeting with you?

332
00:25:55,280 --> 00:25:56,720
No.

333
00:25:56,720 --> 00:25:59,160
I hope he's tied up with some big case

334
00:25:59,160 --> 00:26:01,840
and has no time for video conferences.

335
00:26:01,840 --> 00:26:05,066
Or I'll feel proctored like a student.

336
00:26:07,480 --> 00:26:08,680
It's not impossible.

337
00:26:08,680 --> 00:26:10,177
I checked his profile.

338
00:26:10,177 --> 00:26:12,160
The SG infringement case he handled in the US

339
00:26:12,160 --> 00:26:14,759
was a sensation in foreign media back then.

340
00:26:14,759 --> 00:26:17,200
They said the young, outstanding Lawyer Xu

341
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:21,319
single-handedly brought SG back to life.

342
00:26:21,319 --> 00:26:24,880
Word has it that the fees SG pays him
as a legal counselor

343
00:26:24,880 --> 00:26:28,520
can cover a well-off life.

344
00:26:28,520 --> 00:26:30,880
He's that impressive?

345
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:33,400
Then my long unrequited love wasn't in vain.

346
00:26:33,400 --> 00:26:35,640
It proves my good taste.

347
00:26:35,640 --> 00:26:37,880
Good taste isn't enough.

348
00:26:37,880 --> 00:26:39,640
He's so smart.

349
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:42,419
Are you sure you didn't slip up?

350
00:26:44,559 --> 00:26:46,720
Missy, thank you. We'll try it ourselves.

351
00:26:46,720 --> 00:26:48,560
Okay.

352
00:26:51,840 --> 00:26:53,840
Not yet.

353
00:26:53,840 --> 00:26:55,880
Listen, in order not to slip up,

354
00:26:55,880 --> 00:26:58,320
I'm in a constant,
exhausting battle of wits with him.

355
00:26:58,320 --> 00:27:01,966
A video call is like an 800-meter race.

356
00:27:01,966 --> 00:27:04,400
But after so many years,

357
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:07,000
he hasn't changed much.

358
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:11,580
I notice a lingering affection in your tone.

359
00:27:14,480 --> 00:27:16,700
No, there isn't.

360
00:27:17,885 --> 00:27:19,320
There isn't?

361
00:27:19,320 --> 00:27:22,040
Every time you mention Xu Huai Song,

362
00:27:22,040 --> 00:27:25,626
your emotional fluctuations
are like those at 18.

363
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:29,680
Everyone has emotional fluctuations

364
00:27:29,680 --> 00:27:31,880
in such an unusual case.

365
00:27:31,880 --> 00:27:32,920
Besides,

366
00:27:32,920 --> 00:27:34,640
unlike at 18,

367
00:27:34,640 --> 00:27:36,400
hormone isn't enough

368
00:27:36,400 --> 00:27:39,160
for love at 28.

369
00:27:39,160 --> 00:27:41,920
It requires physical attraction,

370
00:27:41,920 --> 00:27:43,800
personal charisma,

371
00:27:43,800 --> 00:27:45,880
shared values,

372
00:27:45,880 --> 00:27:47,717
and resonance,

373
00:27:47,717 --> 00:27:50,606
all of which are essential.

374
00:27:51,846 --> 00:27:53,960
My current emotional fluctuations

375
00:27:53,960 --> 00:27:56,680
are far from rekindling old flames.

376
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:59,359
At most, it's just

377
00:27:59,359 --> 00:28:01,840
reminiscing about my youth,

378
00:28:01,840 --> 00:28:04,120
and missing the person

379
00:28:04,120 --> 00:28:06,480
I used to be back then.

380
00:28:06,480 --> 00:28:08,440
A writer's tone.

381
00:28:08,440 --> 00:28:10,320
All of which are essential,

382
00:28:10,320 --> 00:28:12,519
reminiscing and missing.

383
00:28:12,519 --> 00:28:14,880
You've made a very clean break.

384
00:28:14,880 --> 00:28:17,440
But you loved him so much.

385
00:28:17,440 --> 00:28:18,843
Don't you feel a sense of closeness

386
00:28:18,843 --> 00:28:21,246
when meeting again?

387
00:28:22,840 --> 00:28:25,160
Worrying about slipping up every day,

388
00:28:25,160 --> 00:28:28,000
I daren't feel that!

389
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:29,120
Besides,

390
00:28:29,120 --> 00:28:31,160
it's been ten years.

391
00:28:31,160 --> 00:28:32,640
Now I only regard him

392
00:28:32,640 --> 00:28:35,319
as a good, responsible lawyer.

393
00:28:35,319 --> 00:28:36,760
I'd rather he weren't so responsible

394
00:28:36,760 --> 00:28:40,080
and handed my case over to Lawyer Liu instead.

395
00:28:40,080 --> 00:28:41,559
What about Lawyer Liu then?

396
00:28:41,559 --> 00:28:43,480
After all these days,

397
00:28:43,480 --> 00:28:45,599
do you have any

398
00:28:45,599 --> 00:28:48,139
spark of love?

399
00:28:49,360 --> 00:28:51,759
I'm not in that mood.

400
00:28:51,759 --> 00:28:53,240
Even if I want,

401
00:28:53,240 --> 00:28:55,520
he is not my type.

402
00:28:55,520 --> 00:28:58,160
You never know unless you try.

403
00:28:58,160 --> 00:29:00,840
I disliked Zhang Chuan at first.

404
00:29:00,840 --> 00:29:02,899
But now?

405
00:29:03,480 --> 00:29:05,760
So sweet!

406
00:29:05,760 --> 00:29:07,286
It does smell good.

407
00:29:07,286 --> 00:29:09,200
Hey, one bottle of this, please.

408
00:29:09,200 --> 00:29:10,513
- Thanks.
- Sure.

409
00:29:17,240 --> 00:29:19,000
What's wrong?

410
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:20,760
I feel like we're being watched.

411
00:29:20,760 --> 00:29:22,359
It's creepy.

412
00:29:22,359 --> 00:29:23,800
In broad daylight,

413
00:29:23,800 --> 00:29:27,020
you switch from a romance to a horror?

414
00:29:27,020 --> 00:29:28,392
Pick one.

415
00:29:28,392 --> 00:29:29,640
- Which one?
- I'm done.

416
00:29:29,640 --> 00:29:31,880
- This one.
- Senior Ruan?

417
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:34,240
It really is you!

418
00:29:45,480 --> 00:29:47,600
You are...

419
00:29:47,600 --> 00:29:49,319
I'm Cen Si Si, Senior.

420
00:29:49,319 --> 00:29:51,333
Don't you remember me?

421
00:30:01,160 --> 00:30:02,723
Oh my god, Senior.

422
00:30:02,723 --> 00:30:04,960
It's been so long since I last saw you.

423
00:30:04,960 --> 00:30:06,480
I peeked over,

424
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:08,920
worried I'd get you wrong.

425
00:30:08,920 --> 00:30:11,120
So you stayed in Hang City after graduation?

426
00:30:11,120 --> 00:30:13,120
Yes.

427
00:30:13,120 --> 00:30:15,040
This is Cen Si Si, our junior,

428
00:30:15,040 --> 00:30:16,813
a Chinese major like me.

429
00:30:16,813 --> 00:30:18,599
This is my best friend, Shen Ming Ying.

430
00:30:18,599 --> 00:30:20,846
- Hello.
- Hello, Senior Shen.

431
00:30:21,920 --> 00:30:23,360
I remember now.

432
00:30:23,360 --> 00:30:27,819
You, Ruan Yu and Shi Can
were in the Arts Department, right?

433
00:30:30,120 --> 00:30:32,000
Shi Can and I are childhood friends.

434
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:33,240
When I went to him,

435
00:30:33,240 --> 00:30:35,453
I saw you many times.

436
00:30:35,453 --> 00:30:38,320
You three were always there.

437
00:30:38,320 --> 00:30:39,913
Those were the days.

438
00:30:39,913 --> 00:30:41,000
By the way,

439
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:43,320
he has a show here these days.

440
00:30:43,320 --> 00:30:45,840
Haven't you planned to meet up?

441
00:30:45,840 --> 00:30:48,200
We aren't in touch much now.

442
00:30:48,200 --> 00:30:49,946
We didn't know his schedule.

443
00:30:51,240 --> 00:30:53,880
Indeed, since he returned to China last year,

444
00:30:53,880 --> 00:30:55,240
he's been quite busy.

445
00:30:55,240 --> 00:30:57,880
Even his family seldom see him.

446
00:30:57,880 --> 00:30:59,200
Yet however busy he gets,

447
00:30:59,200 --> 00:31:01,513
he shouldn't forget old friends, right?

448
00:31:01,513 --> 00:31:02,800
Tell you what,

449
00:31:02,800 --> 00:31:05,809
I check his schedule
and arrange for our reunion,

450
00:31:05,809 --> 00:31:07,653
okay?

451
00:31:10,286 --> 00:31:11,440
Senior,

452
00:31:11,440 --> 00:31:14,160
what do you do now?

453
00:31:14,160 --> 00:31:16,700
I'm a freelancer, I guess.

454
00:31:17,480 --> 00:31:20,320
You aren't a writer, are you?

455
00:31:21,520 --> 00:31:22,800
Not really.

456
00:31:22,800 --> 00:31:24,257
Just a scribbler.

457
00:31:24,257 --> 00:31:27,920
And you? What have you done since graduation?

458
00:31:27,920 --> 00:31:29,720
Me?

459
00:31:29,720 --> 00:31:33,320
I work for my family's company.

460
00:31:34,760 --> 00:31:37,313
But our college is a cradle of talent,

461
00:31:37,313 --> 00:31:39,080
nurturing superstars like Shi Can

462
00:31:39,080 --> 00:31:41,240
and famous writers like you.

463
00:31:41,240 --> 00:31:44,740
Actually, I know a few web novelists.

464
00:31:44,740 --> 00:31:47,640
It seems a tough profession.

465
00:31:47,640 --> 00:31:49,720
They all have it pretty hard.

466
00:31:49,720 --> 00:31:50,910
I'm doing okay.

467
00:31:50,910 --> 00:31:52,079
I'm pretty laid-back,

468
00:31:52,079 --> 00:31:54,480
happy with what I write.

469
00:31:54,480 --> 00:31:57,933
Indeed, cyberspace is harsh now.

470
00:31:57,933 --> 00:32:00,573
It's good you don't let it get to you.

471
00:32:05,016 --> 00:32:08,136
[Xu Huai Song]

472
00:32:09,520 --> 00:32:10,880
Sorry, I have to take this call.

473
00:32:10,880 --> 00:32:13,760
Don't worry. Go ahead.

474
00:32:17,040 --> 00:32:18,200
Lawyer Xu.

475
00:32:18,200 --> 00:32:20,200
<i>Notice from the court,</i>

476
00:32:20,200 --> 00:32:23,220
your case has progressed to adding defendants.

477
00:32:23,220 --> 00:32:25,400
That fast?

478
00:32:25,400 --> 00:32:27,400
Lawyer Xu, it must be late where you are.

479
00:32:27,400 --> 00:32:28,880
Are you still at work?

480
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:30,686
Insomnia, as usual.

481
00:32:32,520 --> 00:32:34,760
I'm calling to ask you something.

482
00:32:34,760 --> 00:32:36,800
I don't know if it's a coincidence,

483
00:32:36,800 --> 00:32:39,440
but you might know the defendant.

484
00:32:39,440 --> 00:32:40,840
I know?

485
00:32:40,840 --> 00:32:42,680
Yes.

486
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:44,520
She was in the same department as you,

487
00:32:44,520 --> 00:32:45,800
two years below you.

488
00:32:45,800 --> 00:32:47,840
From Heng University?

489
00:32:47,840 --> 00:32:49,137
That's right.

490
00:32:49,137 --> 00:32:50,880
Her name is Cen Si Si.

491
00:32:50,880 --> 00:32:52,753
<i>Does that ring a bell?</i>

492
00:32:59,560 --> 00:33:02,266
I'm having dessert with her right now.

493
00:33:03,720 --> 00:33:05,880
From the online slander

494
00:33:05,880 --> 00:33:07,480
to today's encounter,

495
00:33:07,480 --> 00:33:09,859
none were coincidences.

496
00:33:27,080 --> 00:33:29,040
<i>It's a common tactic</i>

497
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:31,880
<i>to plagiarize the ideas of unknown writers</i>

498
00:33:31,880 --> 00:33:34,480
<i>and pay in exchange for their silence.</i>

499
00:33:34,480 --> 00:33:36,000
<i>The fake statement...</i>

500
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:39,080
<i>Wen Xiang is fooling us.</i>

501
00:33:39,080 --> 00:33:40,720
<i>Is her unproductive year</i>

502
00:33:40,720 --> 00:33:41,920
<i>due to writer's block</i>

503
00:33:41,920 --> 00:33:43,759
<i>or a lack of plagiarism source?</i>

504
00:33:43,759 --> 00:33:47,453
<i>Were the previous works written by herself?</i>

505
00:33:50,520 --> 00:33:53,353
Senior, are you okay?

506
00:33:53,353 --> 00:33:54,400
What's wrong?

507
00:33:54,400 --> 00:33:55,440
Feeling unwell?

508
00:33:55,440 --> 00:33:58,260
You look pale.

509
00:33:59,760 --> 00:34:01,240
Senior?

510
00:34:01,240 --> 00:34:02,573
What's the matter?

511
00:34:02,573 --> 00:34:04,700
Are you all right?

512
00:34:06,480 --> 00:34:07,960
Junior,

513
00:34:07,960 --> 00:34:11,346
is your Qianhe ID Su Cheng?

514
00:34:15,120 --> 00:34:16,352
You...

515
00:34:16,352 --> 00:34:19,606
Senior, are you psychic?

516
00:34:21,120 --> 00:34:22,726
I'm not psychic.

517
00:34:22,726 --> 00:34:24,726
I'm Wen Xiang.

518
00:34:26,480 --> 00:34:28,488
<i>A showdown?</i>

519
00:34:28,488 --> 00:34:30,000
<i>How about I have a judge here</i>

520
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:31,740
<i>to hold a trial for you two?</i>

521
00:34:35,120 --> 00:34:36,280
Senior,

522
00:34:36,280 --> 00:34:39,080
are you joking?

523
00:34:48,776 --> 00:34:51,686
[Wen Xiang]

524
00:34:55,360 --> 00:34:58,360
It's a small world.

525
00:34:58,360 --> 00:35:00,800
Well, on Weibo, I...

526
00:35:03,440 --> 00:35:04,760
Oh my god.

527
00:35:04,760 --> 00:35:05,880
Oh my god, oh my god.

528
00:35:05,880 --> 00:35:08,520
I need to calm down.

529
00:35:13,360 --> 00:35:15,680
Senior, no, look.

530
00:35:15,680 --> 00:35:18,920
It's a huge misunderstanding.

531
00:35:18,920 --> 00:35:20,800
Had I known you were Wen Xiang,

532
00:35:20,800 --> 00:35:23,533
I wouldn't have posted that.

533
00:35:25,480 --> 00:35:27,318
- Really?
- Yes.

534
00:35:27,318 --> 00:35:28,560
Why?

535
00:35:28,560 --> 00:35:31,760
Because you definitely wouldn't plagiarize!

536
00:35:32,800 --> 00:35:34,520
Senior,

537
00:35:34,520 --> 00:35:36,733
did you sue me?

538
00:35:40,200 --> 00:35:41,840
Look,

539
00:35:41,840 --> 00:35:43,613
this misunderstanding is huge.

540
00:35:43,613 --> 00:35:45,800
Had I known you were Su Cheng,

541
00:35:45,800 --> 00:35:47,360
I...

542
00:35:47,360 --> 00:35:49,979
<i>would have sued you sooner.</i>

543
00:35:50,719 --> 00:35:53,713
It was my fault anyway, Senior.

544
00:35:54,880 --> 00:35:56,840
I didn't want to make a big deal of it.

545
00:35:56,840 --> 00:35:58,716
If you think it's a misunderstanding,

546
00:35:58,716 --> 00:35:59,960
we can settle.

547
00:35:59,960 --> 00:36:01,960
Really, Senior?

548
00:36:01,960 --> 00:36:03,480
That'd be great!

549
00:36:03,480 --> 00:36:07,160
If my dad knew, he'd scold me to death.

550
00:36:07,160 --> 00:36:09,560
If Shi Can knew,

551
00:36:09,560 --> 00:36:12,539
he'd feel so awkward.

552
00:36:15,719 --> 00:36:16,760
Senior,

553
00:36:16,760 --> 00:36:18,280
if you could forgive me,

554
00:36:18,280 --> 00:36:19,840
I'll definitely apologize publicly,

555
00:36:19,840 --> 00:36:21,840
try to eliminate all the negative impact,

556
00:36:21,840 --> 00:36:23,800
never do such stupid things again,

557
00:36:23,800 --> 00:36:25,880
and do anything for you.

558
00:36:25,880 --> 00:36:28,880
<i>So you do know you've been a terrible person.</i>

559
00:36:28,880 --> 00:36:30,353
It's not a big deal.

560
00:36:30,353 --> 00:36:34,073
But I don't know much about settlement.

561
00:36:39,040 --> 00:36:40,800
Settlement certainly requires a lawyer.

562
00:36:40,800 --> 00:36:41,920
But we don't know the procedure.

563
00:36:41,920 --> 00:36:44,680
If anything goes wrong, it'll cause trouble.

564
00:36:44,680 --> 00:36:49,213
Indeed, we can't decide a lawsuit on our own.

565
00:36:51,120 --> 00:36:53,600
Are you free tomorrow?

566
00:36:53,600 --> 00:36:56,080
Tomorrow?

567
00:36:56,080 --> 00:36:57,800
I...

568
00:36:57,800 --> 00:37:00,320
I might be in meetings all day tomorrow,

569
00:37:00,320 --> 00:37:01,920
and I cannot leave.

570
00:37:01,920 --> 00:37:04,199
Senior, how about the day after tomorrow?

571
00:37:04,199 --> 00:37:06,046
That works.

572
00:37:06,046 --> 00:37:07,200
And...

573
00:37:07,200 --> 00:37:08,983
the court?

574
00:37:08,983 --> 00:37:10,719
I'll inform them of the delay.

575
00:37:10,719 --> 00:37:12,899
No worries.

576
00:37:13,800 --> 00:37:15,640
Add on WeChat to keep in touch.

577
00:37:15,640 --> 00:37:17,520
Okay.

578
00:37:30,000 --> 00:37:32,520
[Conversation with Su Cheng]
<i>A transcript of my conversation with Su Cheng</i>

579
00:37:32,520 --> 00:37:34,953
<i>for your review.</i>

580
00:37:38,080 --> 00:37:39,520
<i>Judging from it,</i>

581
00:37:39,520 --> 00:37:42,886
<i>Cen Si Si may really not know you're Wen Xiang.</i>

582
00:38:03,160 --> 00:38:05,141
<i>Not necessarily.</i>

583
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:07,600
<i>It's a bit complicated.</i>

584
00:38:07,600 --> 00:38:09,120
<i>Let's talk in person tomorrow.</i>

585
00:38:09,120 --> 00:38:11,600
<i>What time works for you two?</i>

586
00:38:16,840 --> 00:38:19,760
<i>Is 1:00 p.m. tomorrow okay?</i>

587
00:38:19,760 --> 00:38:21,360
<i>That works for me.</i>

588
00:38:21,360 --> 00:38:23,580
<i>Lawyer Xu?</i>

589
00:38:30,040 --> 00:38:32,581
<i>Let's push it back four hours.</i>

590
00:38:33,920 --> 00:38:36,500
<i>It'd be midnight for you then.</i>

591
00:38:37,800 --> 00:38:39,280
<i>Any time is fine with me.</i>

592
00:38:39,280 --> 00:38:41,920
<i>Let's go with Lawyer Xu's schedule.</i>

593
00:38:43,080 --> 00:38:44,537
<i>Okay, Ruan Yu.</i>

594
00:38:44,537 --> 00:38:47,246
<i>See you at the firm at 5:00 p.m. tomorrow.</i>

595
00:38:53,800 --> 00:38:55,080
Thank you.

596
00:38:55,080 --> 00:38:56,320
Thank you.

597
00:38:56,320 --> 00:38:58,226
Okay, this way.

598
00:39:03,199 --> 00:39:05,140
Lawyer Xu.

599
00:39:05,760 --> 00:39:06,960
Thank you so much.

600
00:39:06,960 --> 00:39:08,400
Without you,

601
00:39:08,400 --> 00:39:10,640
a foreign lawsuit

602
00:39:10,640 --> 00:39:13,239
might be unfair to us.

603
00:39:13,239 --> 00:39:14,679
Law is here

604
00:39:14,679 --> 00:39:16,199
to justly protect

605
00:39:16,199 --> 00:39:18,599
and save the innocent.

606
00:39:18,599 --> 00:39:21,679
That's what we lawyers should do.

607
00:39:21,679 --> 00:39:23,680
That may be so.

608
00:39:23,680 --> 00:39:25,639
But we're penniless employees.

609
00:39:25,639 --> 00:39:28,360
Only you took our case pro bono,

610
00:39:28,360 --> 00:39:30,670
and did so much preparatory work.

611
00:39:30,670 --> 00:39:32,640
In a word, thanks!

612
00:39:32,640 --> 00:39:34,480
Thank you.

613
00:39:34,480 --> 00:39:35,840
When you're abroad,

614
00:39:35,840 --> 00:39:37,760
you can trust your fellow countrymen.

615
00:39:37,760 --> 00:39:38,960
Alright.

616
00:39:38,960 --> 00:39:40,360
I won't keep you from your work.

617
00:39:40,360 --> 00:39:42,260
I'll head out now.

618
00:39:55,760 --> 00:39:58,000
- Hello?
<i>- Hey, Song!</i>

619
00:39:58,000 --> 00:39:59,360
I'm so mad!

620
00:39:59,360 --> 00:40:01,199
Su Cheng instigated me

621
00:40:01,199 --> 00:40:03,180
to sue Ruan Yu.

622
00:40:04,280 --> 00:40:06,840
I'll send you the screenshot.

623
00:40:08,800 --> 00:40:10,079
<i>After consideration,</i>

624
00:40:10,079 --> 00:40:11,800
<i>I still suggest you sue Wen Xiang.</i>

625
00:40:11,800 --> 00:40:14,320
<i>After all, she violated your copyright.</i>

626
00:40:14,320 --> 00:40:16,719
<i>Missy, as a newbie in the web novel market,</i>

627
00:40:16,719 --> 00:40:18,600
<i>you have no idea</i>

628
00:40:18,600 --> 00:40:21,800
<i>how much her plagiarism will harm you.</i>

629
00:40:21,800 --> 00:40:24,200
See?

630
00:40:24,200 --> 00:40:26,200
What should I do?

631
00:40:26,200 --> 00:40:28,079
Ask her to prove that

632
00:40:28,079 --> 00:40:30,580
she is Su Cheng.

633
00:40:47,000 --> 00:40:48,960
Lawyer Xu must be asleep.

634
00:40:48,960 --> 00:40:50,793
It's wee hours there.

635
00:40:51,800 --> 00:40:54,060
True. Let's not wait for him then.

636
00:40:54,060 --> 00:40:55,800
No worries. Lawyer Xu is absent.

637
00:40:55,800 --> 00:40:57,383
We still have Lawyer Liu,

638
00:40:57,383 --> 00:40:58,720
right?

639
00:40:58,720 --> 00:41:00,520
From where we left off?

640
00:41:00,520 --> 00:41:02,560
Okay.

641
00:41:03,639 --> 00:41:06,600
Cen Si Si seemed to try too hard.

642
00:41:06,600 --> 00:41:08,600
When I told her that I was Wen Xiang,

643
00:41:08,600 --> 00:41:10,760
her chin slammed into the glass,

644
00:41:10,760 --> 00:41:12,960
and she hurt so much that she shedded tears.

645
00:41:12,960 --> 00:41:15,080
She rubbed her eyes and asked,

646
00:41:15,080 --> 00:41:16,933
"Are you joking?"

647
00:41:16,933 --> 00:41:18,657
And after she was exposed,

648
00:41:18,657 --> 00:41:19,800
she flushed

649
00:41:19,800 --> 00:41:21,520
and fanned herself frantically.

650
00:41:21,520 --> 00:41:23,640
Those acts

651
00:41:23,640 --> 00:41:25,440
made her look shocked then.

652
00:41:25,440 --> 00:41:26,537
But,

653
00:41:26,537 --> 00:41:29,020
the more I think about it,
the more I feel something was off.

654
00:41:29,020 --> 00:41:31,396
You mean she was acting?

655
00:41:31,396 --> 00:41:32,480
Yes.

656
00:41:32,480 --> 00:41:36,119
She probably didn't expect my showdown.

657
00:41:36,119 --> 00:41:38,720
So those exaggerated acts,

658
00:41:38,720 --> 00:41:41,239
I think, were to divert my attention

659
00:41:41,239 --> 00:41:44,160
and buy herself some time to react.

660
00:41:44,160 --> 00:41:45,753
Yes.

661
00:41:46,920 --> 00:41:49,000
So,

662
00:41:49,000 --> 00:41:51,473
I think she has another move planned.

663
00:41:52,052 --> 00:41:53,120
Another move?

664
00:41:53,120 --> 00:41:54,800
Yes.

665
00:41:54,800 --> 00:41:55,960
No way.

666
00:41:55,960 --> 00:41:57,440
How could she have another move?

667
00:41:57,440 --> 00:42:00,653
Are you writers just too imaginative?

668
00:42:02,400 --> 00:42:05,833
But her acts made me...

669
00:42:09,800 --> 00:42:11,039
Xu...

670
00:42:11,039 --> 00:42:13,379
Lawyer Xu!

671
00:42:15,520 --> 00:42:17,559
Why are you back in the country?

672
00:42:17,559 --> 00:42:20,060
You said "See you at the firm."

673
00:42:24,520 --> 00:42:26,660
What is this?

674
00:42:27,320 --> 00:42:30,180
Cen Si Si's another move.

675
00:42:54,920 --> 00:42:57,039
<i>Let's eat fried chicken this afternoon.</i>

676
00:42:57,039 --> 00:42:58,240
<i>Sure.</i>

677
00:42:58,240 --> 00:42:59,497
<i>Fried chicken? Xu,</i>

678
00:42:59,497 --> 00:43:01,200
<i>is it proper for a smart, well-behaved</i>

679
00:43:01,200 --> 00:43:03,593
<i>student like you to take the lead?</i>

680
00:43:03,593 --> 00:43:04,760
<i>In or not?</i>

681
00:43:04,760 --> 00:43:07,120
<i>I'm in!</i>

682
00:43:07,120 --> 00:43:10,320
<i>Put a ladder at the postern</i>

683
00:43:10,320 --> 00:43:12,480
<i>after school.</i>

684
00:43:12,480 --> 00:43:14,400
<i>Ladder? What for?</i>

685
00:43:14,400 --> 00:43:15,800
<i>Find a ladder</i>

686
00:43:15,800 --> 00:43:17,840
<i>and put it at the postern.</i>

687
00:43:17,840 --> 00:43:19,040
<i>What are you talking about?</i>

688
00:43:19,040 --> 00:43:20,280
<i>You know it!</i>

689
00:43:20,280 --> 00:43:22,719
<i>Climbing over the wall to buy fried chicken.</i>

690
00:43:22,719 --> 00:43:23,993
<i>Have you finished your homework?</i>

691
00:43:23,993 --> 00:43:25,120
<i>I'm not interested.</i>

692
00:43:25,120 --> 00:43:26,760
<i>- Study?
- Forget the homework!</i>

693
00:43:26,760 --> 00:43:29,519
<i>Go for fried chicken.</i>

694
00:43:29,519 --> 00:43:31,719
<i>What's the deal? Are you eating or not?</i>

695
00:43:31,719 --> 00:43:33,440
<i>Let's go! They'll close soon.</i>

696
00:43:33,440 --> 00:43:34,800
<i>You're in charge of the ladder!</i>

697
00:43:34,800 --> 00:43:37,506
<i>How can you be like this?</i>

698
00:43:37,506 --> 00:43:38,800
<i>It's a deal then.</i>

699
00:43:38,800 --> 00:43:40,920
<i>Hey, you guys.</i>

700
00:43:40,920 --> 00:43:43,320
<i>A lower tone won't hurt.</i>

701
00:43:43,320 --> 00:43:45,079
<i>But that's the way we talk.</i>

702
00:43:45,079 --> 00:43:47,040
<i>We've always been this loud.</i>

703
00:43:47,040 --> 00:43:48,552
<i>You never complained before.</i>

704
00:43:48,552 --> 00:43:49,760
<i>Don't you talk like this too?</i>

705
00:43:49,760 --> 00:43:52,440
<i>Are we going or not?</i>

706
00:43:52,440 --> 00:43:53,960
<i>- Go.
- Go?</i>

707
00:43:53,960 --> 00:43:56,490
<i>Go!</i>

